 Harold Bradley, chief investment 
officer at the Ewing Marion Kauffman Foundation, told the Senate
Subcommittee on Securities, Insurance and Investment that 
exchange-traded products have negatively impacted capital 
markets.  Eric Noll, executive vice president from Nasdaq OMX, 
was among those who offered a different viewpoint.  Bloomberg 
Radio's Catherine Cowdery reports on Exchange Traded Funds.   (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 01:37
 